OL,3,CShould the Channel Islands apply to
OL,4,Cturn their towns into cities?
OL,6,FThe Constable of St Helier, Simon
OL,7,FCrowcroft, has been pushing for city
OL,8,Fstatus since 2001, but admits the idea
OL,9,Fhasn't gained much traction: "It's not
OL,10,Fa case perhaps of people opposing it
OL,11,Fbut certainly when I've taken
OL,12,Fsoundings in the past, there just
OL,13,Fhasn't been much enthusiasm.
OL,15,F"Maybe there have been other things
OL,16,Fgoing on which are a more pressing
OL,17,Fconcern to residents."
