OL,3,CShould the Channel Islands apply to
OL,4,Cturn their towns into cities?
OL,6,F"We are a small town on a beautiful
OL,7,Fisland, being a city would make
OL,8,Fvarious demands on us with perhaps
OL,9,Ffinancial implications which we don't
OL,10,Fwant and the paperwork was ludicrous".
OL,12,FThe application process is available
OL,13,Fevery 10 years in line with the
OL,14,Fmonarch's jubilee, whereby applicants
OL,15,Fcan bid for free to be granted the
OL,16,Fstatus.
OL,18,FA committee manages the bids, but the
OL,19,Fmonarch officially grants the city
OL,20,Fstatus by a document known as the
OL,21,F'letters patent'.
